---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHero from '../../components/SectionHero.astro';
import ContentCTA from '../../components/ContentCTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Best Email Security Gateway for SMB 2026"
  description="Compare Mimecast, Proofpoint, Barracuda, SpamTitan & Avanan. Block phishing and malware before it reaches your team."
>
  <SectionHero
    icon="📧"
    title="Email Security Gateway Comparison"
    description="90% of cyberattacks start with email. Your built-in spam filter is not enough. Here are the email security gateways that actually stop phishing, business email compromise, and malware — at small business prices."
    badge="⭐ Honest Review · FTC Affiliate Disclosure"
    gradient="from-primary-950 via-primary-900 to-red-950"
  />

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <div class="rounded-xl bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 p-4 text-sm text-yellow-800 mb-10">
        <strong>⚖️ Affiliate Disclosure:</strong> Some links may be affiliate links. Ratings are independent and based on our testing.
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Why Built-in Spam Filters Are Not Enough</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Google Workspace and Microsoft 365 include spam filtering. It catches the obvious stuff — Nigerian prince emails, Viagra ads, obvious malware attachments. It does NOT catch targeted phishing emails impersonating your CEO, fake invoice emails from "vendors you know," or credential harvesting pages hosted on legitimate services. For that, you need a dedicated email security gateway that analyzes sender reputation, link destinations, attachment behavior, and language patterns using AI.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="min-w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-50">
            <tr><th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Product</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Starting Price</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">AI Detection</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Link Protection</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Best For</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Avanan</td><td class="text-center">$3-5/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700">✅ Advanced AI</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700">✅ Time-of-click</td><td class="text-center">M365/Google Workspace users</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Proofpoint Essentials</td><td class="text-center">$3-4/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700">✅ ML-based</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700">✅ URL defense</td><td class="text-center">Enterprise-grade at SMB price</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Mimecast</td><td class="text-center">$3-5/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700">✅ Targeted threat</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700">✅ URL protect</td><td class="text-center">Larger SMBs, compliance needs</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Barracuda</td><td class="text-center">$2.50/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700">✅ AI-based</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700">✅ Link protect</td><td class="text-center">Best budget option</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">SpamTitan</td><td class="text-center">$2/user/month</td><td class="text-center">✅ Basic ML</td><td class="text-center">✅</td><td class="text-center">Lowest cost, basic needs</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10">Detailed Reviews</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">1. Avanan — Best AI-Powered Detection</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Avanan (acquired by Check Point) takes a unique API-based approach — it sits inside your Microsoft 365 or Google Workspace tenant via API integration, not as an SMTP gateway. Deployment takes 5 minutes with no MX record changes. Its AI engine is trained on trillions of emails and catches sophisticated attacks including business email compromise, account takeover, and credential harvesting that bypass traditional filters. At $3-5/user/month, it is priced competitively with enterprise options. Avanan is our top pick for most small businesses.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">2. Proofpoint Essentials — Enterprise Tech, SMB Package</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Proofpoint protects most Fortune 500 companies. Proofpoint Essentials is the same technology packaged for small business at $3-4/user/month. It includes URL defense (rewrites and scans links at click time), attachment sandboxing (detonates suspicious attachments in a virtual environment), and impostor detection (flags emails pretending to be from your CEO). If you want the most proven enterprise email security at SMB prices, Proofpoint delivers.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">3. Mimecast — Best for Compliance & Archiving</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Mimecast combines email security with email archiving, continuity (access email even if M365 goes down), and compliance features. For businesses in regulated industries (legal, finance, healthcare) that need email retention and e-discovery capabilities, Mimecast provides security + compliance in one platform. Pricing is higher and the feature set is broader than most small businesses need — but if you need archiving anyway, the bundle makes sense.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">4. Barracuda Email Protection — Best Budget Option</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">At $2.50/user/month, Barracuda offers solid AI-based phishing detection, link protection, and attachment sandboxing at the lowest price among full-featured options. It lacks some of the advanced AI sophistication of Avanan and Proofpoint, but catches the vast majority of threats. A good choice if budget is the primary concern but you still want dedicated email security beyond the built-in filter.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">5. SpamTitan — Lowest Cost, Basic Protection</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">SpamTitan is the cheapest option at ~$2/user/month. It uses dual antivirus engines (Bitdefender + ClamAV) plus basic machine learning for spam and phishing detection. It lacks the sophisticated AI-based BEC detection of Avanan and Proofpoint, but provides solid protection against known threats, spam, and malware. Best for businesses that want to add a layer of email security beyond the built-in filter at minimal cost.</p>

      <ContentCTA
        icon="🎣"
        title="Test Your Team's Phishing Detection Skills"
        description="Our free phishing quiz presents 10 real-world email scenarios. See which ones trick your team — and which ones you catch."
        href="/tools/phishing-quiz/"
        ctaText="Take the Phishing Quiz →"
      />

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10">Our Recommendation</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li><strong>🟢 Best for most small businesses:</strong> Avanan — 5-minute setup, best AI detection, $3-5/user/month</li>
          <li><strong>🟢 Enterprise-grade at SMB price:</strong> Proofpoint Essentials — same tech Fortune 500 uses</li>
          <li><strong>🟡 Need email archiving + compliance too:</strong> Mimecast — security + continuity + archiving</li>
          <li><strong>🟢 Tightest budget:</strong> Barracuda ($2.50) or SpamTitan ($2/user/month)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
